{
  "stem": "15732.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we couldn't get any other-- What I didn't say before is that the Romanian administration, when they came back, in order to establish themself again in Czernowitz, they needed people who knew how to go along, how-- how to administer, and how to make things work.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they gave certain people that were necessary for them, they gave them exemptions.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Some, even, that they needed badly, were even exempt of being in the-- in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I had an uncle who was very high functional in the-- the railway.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He really knew his job.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he got a exemption.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he had even allowed-- was allowed to be out of the ghetto and to go back to his house.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We couldn't buy ourself something like that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So the best my father could do was buy himself that he's not transferable.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So when the next wave started, we had once that they came up to our place and told us to go out.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I showed them the-- the certificate.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They looked at my father.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My father was really, very sick.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So they didn't take us away, which was great, great luck that they still acknowledged that piece of paper.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But we knew that the second time, we wouldn't get away with it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were Romanians.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As far as I can remember-- memory dims after so many years-- there was always somebody from the security.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were two soldiers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a policeman.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was a group that came and they just told you all you can-- could take was a rucksack, a knapsack, with just a few things.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then you were made to walk a long, quite a long distance, the group getting bigger and bigger and bigger.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
